5:
I see... So you two saved me and
brought me here. I owe you my life.
9:
H-hey, it's no big deal. We're friends,
after all.
13:
No, I really am grateful. You're
stranded on this island, but you still
made the effort to look out for
someone else. I really appreciate it.
18:
A-Alk, something's wrong! Sohvi's
acting... normal!
23:
Yeah, this conversation feels all sorts
of wrong... Wait, those ears...
27:
Uh, anyway... Just how much do you
remember, Sohvi?
30:
Let's see... I know my own name and
that I've worked in a lab, but that's
about it.
33:
When I came to, I was in an
unfamiliar building.
35:
I tried to leave, but as soon as I
stepped foot outside, I was chased
by a terrifying monster. I ran like my
life depended on it...
37:
That must have been when I lost
consciousness. The next thing I
know, I'm on the beach with you two.
42: Gotcha... Well, at least you're okay.
46:
Do you remember anything about
the building you were in? Were there
other people inside?
51: Um... Sorry, I can't say for sure...
54:
But it did seem like a
state-of-the-art facility. What else
can I remem—
58:
Huh? Wh-why is my hair so long? It
wasn't... like this before...
61:
That's right... There was blood...
b-blood, blood! It won't stop... 
I-I need to take the medicine!
65:
It's still incomplete, but it will work. It
MUST work! I CAN'T die here!
72:
Th-that's right... The medicine. 
If I can finish it... 
Mama and Papa will… A-ah...
82: Sohvi, calm down! You're safe! Stop!
91:
Sorry... You don't have to force
yourself to remember.
99:
Thank you for the delicious meal!
Food tastes extra good on an empty
stomach.
102:
But... I'm sorry for all the trouble I've
caused you.
105:
You're no trouble at all! It's actually
reassuring to have another friend
with us.
108:
Th-that's not what I mean. I just...
feel like I'm getting in the way of
your alone time...
111:
...Huh? Wait, you two are lovers,
aren't you?
124:
Love is that unstable, crazed
emotional state that befalls
outsiders before marriage, correct?
128: I mean, I wouldn't put it like that...
131:
I don't really understand the
concept of love.
134:
Even if I did... I've lost my powers as a
priestess...
136:
I am no longer qualified to stand by
your side as your wyfu, Alk...
141:
What do your powers have to do
with anything?
149:
You're YOU, Shywe. You don't need
anything special to stand beside me.
153:
Ah, I mean as a FRIEND, of course!
Definitely not agreeing to be your
hazubando! Nope!
161: I really don't understand you at all...
169:
Urgh... Yep, it's official. I'm a total
third-wheel here!
173:
But I have to say, I'm a little jealous! 
I can't wait to find myself someone 
to love and cherish!
176:
Huh? Did I say something funny? I'm
pretty sure I've been holed up in a
lab most of my life, so I wouldn't
have—
180:
W-wait, don't tell me... Do I actually
have a boyfriend?!
184:
A-anyway, we should head to the
building Sohvi woke up in tomorrow!
189:
What a great idea! We might find
more people there!
194:
H-hold on! Answer my question right
this instant!
197:
Tell me more about my boyfriend!
My precious darling!
205: Dammit... I can't chicken out now!
209:
Nimbus, can you hear me? This is
Light on Paradise Isle.
213: Loud and clear. Did you find 'em?!
216:
No... Not yet. But we may have some
information that can point you in
the right direction.
219:
We've heard tell of a drifting island...
A strange landmass that floats
around like a boat.
221:
That island's projected path lines up
perfectly with Alk and Shywe's last
reported location.
224:
Gotcha. Then we'll head there. Tell
me the coordinates!
228:
The building should be in this
direction, right, Sohvi?
232:
I-I think so! To be honest though, I
was so busy running for my life that
I'm not entirely sure I remember the
route...
236:
Gotcha. Didn't yesterday's prophecy
come from this direction, Shywe?
240:
Get back, you two! Something's
headed our way!
252:
Th-that's the monster that was
chasing me!
256: What?! Wait, but isn't he your—
265:
Oh, come on! Why did it have to be
another one of these things?!
